 the company the buildings were completed in  the company has been the subject of multiple environmental cases including the largest environmental contamination settlement in american history  the  settlement related to the former tronox subsidiary of kerr mcgee a company purchased by anadarko in  contents  current operations  united states  international operations  history  acquisitions and sales  environmental record  deepwater horizon oil spill involvement  settlement with bp  fine under the clean water act  tronox litigation and settlements  lawsuit from tronox shareholders  lawsuit from the environmental protection agency and department of justice  references  external links current operationsedit in addition to exploration and production the company engages in the gathering processing and treating of natural gas and the transporting of natural gas crude oil and natural gas liquids the company also participates in the hard minerals business through its ownership of nonoperated joint ventures and royalty arrangements as of december   the company had approximately  billion barrels of oil equivalent × gj of proved reserves  of which were liquids and  of which were natural gas in  the company produced  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day united statesedit the company’s operations in the united states accounted for  of total sales volumes during  and  of total proved reserves at yearend  in the united states the company has major holdings in the rocky mountains wattenberg gas field  approximately  vertical wells and  horizontal wells laramie county wyoming  denverjulesburg basin  more than  net acres operating  vertical wells and  horizontal wells greater natural buttes utah  approximately  wells powder river basin  over  acres of deep mineral rights greater green river basin  operates  wells southern and appalachia region delaware basin  over  gross acres producing wells are primarily in the cline shale eagle ford   gross acres and over  producing wells